26/03/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Intelligence Service (SRI) is recommending further cross-border assistance aimed at preventing terrorism. On Wednesday (26 March), SRI director Radu Alexandru Timofte said that Romanian intelligence maintains contacts with 70 foreign services in the field from 50 countries. He urged other organisations to join the global network. Wednesday marked the 13th anniversary of SRI, which succeeded Romania's former intelligence structure. (Radio Romania, Rompres - 26/03/03)
